<HEADLINE> Smith to Leave Post in Rangers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, October 28 (Xinhua) -- Scottish champions club Glasgow
Rangers coach Walter Smith was poise to leave his post at the end
of the season, it was reported Tuesday from Glasgow, Sctland.
</P>
<P>
The most possible successor is Finland national coach Richard
Moller-Nielsen, who led Denmark to the 1992 European
Championships, though no official remark has been made, reports
said.
</P>
<P>
Smith, who went into the charge of Rangers in the 1990-91
season, has been pacing an impressive period of the Scottish
league history as Rangers went on to clinch seven league
championships in nine seasons, one title short of the record set
by Celtic in 1966-74.
</P>
<P>
Smith made his decision before the club conceded double
elimination from the Champions' and UEFA Cups. 
</P>
</TEXT>
