<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Shares Close on Largest Point Loss </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 28 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong shares crashed
today, with the benchmark Hang Seng Index shedding 1438.31 points
or 13.7 percent to close at 9059.89, the biggest point loss in its
history.
</P>
<P>
It was widely believed that the crash in Hong Kong stock market
was a reaction to the worldwide market sell-off and in particular,
the largest ever point drop in Dow Jones Industries overnight in
New York.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng Index opened 8.09 percent lower at 9,649 points
today and then slid to new lows because of the shock waves on Wall
Street which stripped 554 points from the Dow Jones Industries.
</P>
<P>
The index closed at 8876.40 points at the mid-day break, a
massive loss of 1621.80 points or 15.45 percent.
</P>
<P>
In the afternoon trading, the market recovered some of the
loss, representing a technical rebound after sharp falls.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong was not the only one feeling the pain. Nearly all
the other regional markets as well as the major European markets
plunged today as investors were getting out of the market.  
</P>
</TEXT>
