<HEADLINE> APEC Symposium Aims to Improve Investment Flows </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 28 (Xinhua) -- The Third Asia-Pacific
Economic Cooperation (APEC) Investment Symposium opened here today
for government officials and business leaders from APEC members to
discuss how to enhance the investment environment in the region.
</P>
<P>
The two-day symposium echoed a call made by the regional
organization in Manila last year to intensify its work on
investment. Participants discussed such issues as how to improve
investment flows in the APEC region and how to make investment
regimes more open and accessible to foreign investors.
</P>
<P>
Other areas of focus included the impact of regulatory reform
on freeing up cross-border investment flows, links between foreign
direct investment and technology transfer and removal of obstacles
to investment in infrastructure and services.
</P>
<P>
Denise Yue, secretary for trade and industry of the Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region (HKSAR), addressed the opening
session of the symposium this morning, urging APEC member
economies to create a better environment for the free flow of
investment.
</P>
<P>
APEC now has 18 member economies from around the Pacific rim.
</P>
</TEXT>
