<HEADLINE> Mongolia Enhances Environmental Protection </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, October 28 (Xinhua) -- Mongolia is improving its
protection over the country's environment by enlarging certain
protected areas. The move is intended to preserve and provide
maximum protection against damage to the country's original
condition.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Nature and Environment said here today that
17.10 million hectares of environmentally protected areas cover 11
percent of the country's territory. There are 26 regions in the
country under protection with the largest one covering 5.3 million
hectares.
</P>
<P>
Each region places particular emphasis on a different theme,
such as the protection of animals, birds, plants and natural
scenes.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, forest and grass fires have seriously damaged
Mongolia's environment. As a result, the ministry has been
working with a dozen international organizations to implement
several environmental protection projects. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
