<HEADLINE> Schmacher Confesses His Errors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, October 28 (Xinhua) -- Michael Schumacher admitted on
Tuesday that he made a mistake in Sunday's Formula One final race,
according to a report.
</P>
<P>
The report said the double world champion told a news
conference at Ferrari headquarters in Maranello, Italy, he made
errors in the crucial race where he drove his Ferrari onto Jacques
Villeneuve's Williams as the later winner of the year overtook him
in the 48th laps.
</P>
<P>
The German was severely criticized for the apparently intended
action by local papers and the people in his motherland. 
</P>
