<HEADLINE> Zambia's Coup Attempt Condemned in Zimbabwe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, October 28 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwean Foreign Affairs
Deputy Minister Nicholas Goche today condemned the attempted coup
against the Zambian government of President Frederick Chiluba.
</P>
<P>
Nicholas Goche said African countries needed to uphold the
stance of the Organisation of African Unity (OAU) to exercise
democracy when it came to change governments.
</P>
<P>
"Change of government should be done through the ballot box.
We totally disapprove of this move," Goche told journalists at
the one day meeting of Foreign Affairs Sub-Committee of the
Zimbabwe-South Africa Joint Commission.
</P>
<P>
The OAU has always been concerned about undemocratic
overthrows of elected governments.
</P>
<P>
Zimbia's State Broadcasting headquarters had been seized this
morning by a man who called himself Captain Solo of the National
Redemption Council. Later Chiluba announced on the radio that
the coup had been crushed and coup plotters arrested.
</P>
<P>
The coup leader said he had taken the action to fight
corruption and crime and end chaos in the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
