<HEADLINE> German Shares Down 8.04 Percent Tuesday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, October 28 (Xinhua) -- German share values lost 8.04 percent
today, in the wake of a 554-point drop in Wall Street Monday followed
by another nosedive on Far Eastern exchanges.
</P>
<P>
This is compared with an over 7 percent loss in early trading.
</P>
<P>
Reports reaching here from Frankfurt said that the main 30-share
DAX index closed at 3,567.22 points, down 311.90 points from Monday's
closing of 3,879.12 in an across-the-board retreat.
</P>
<P>
The broader-based MDAX dropped 257.87 points to close at 3,569.92
points, while bonds continued to rise as investors sought safety for
their money. The REX-Index increased by 0.44 points to a closing of
110.00.
</P>
<P>
Among the day's major losers were carmaker BMW, with shares down
195 marks, or 14.7 percent to 1,125. Daimler-Benz, despite an upbeat
report on 1997 profits outlook, saw its shares drop 12.8 marks to 112
marks. Linde's stocks dropped 110 marks to 990 marks.
</P>
<P>
Traders were in fear of a further collapse on the New York market,
it was reported.  
</P>
