said there is no need to resort to military coups to solve the
pressing problems in the country.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with the Zambia News Agency in Chipata, the
capital of Eastern Province, Andrew Banda said that both the
ruling and opposition parties should not waste time but start
dialogue to sort out their differences to avoid a situation like
the one the country witnessed today.
</P>
