<HEADLINE> Russian Government Approves Budget Revisions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, October 28 (Xinhua) -- The Russian government has
approved today the draft 1998 budget reworked by the tripartite
commission after the Duma turned down the government's budget
version, the Itar-Tass news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Officials of the governmental culture and information
department told a briefing that 1998 gross domestic product target
is two trillion 840 billion re-denominated roubles (one US dollar
equals 5882 roubles).
</P>
<P>
The budget projects revenue of 367.5 billion roubles and
spending of 499.9 billion roubles. The budget deficit, 132.4
billion roubles, is to make 4.7 percent of GDP and 26.5 percent of
the budget's total spending in 1998.
</P>
<P>
Annual inflation is forecast to be 5.7 percent in next year.
</P>
<P>
The budget deficit is to be filled with 30.4 billion roubles
from external and 102 billion roubles from internal sources.
</P>
<P>
The report said that the government has approved ten draft laws
intended to build up the budget's revenue.
</P>
<P>
The laws are to add to federal taxes, on January 1, 1998, taxes
on the water and use of he fauna, and license rates on alcohol
production and sales.
</P>
<P>
The government plans to introduce amendments to the federal law
on taxation of the purchase of foreign currencies. The amended law
is to revise the foreign currency tax from 0.5 to one percent of
the total worth of a deal in the foreign currency, since January
1.
</P>
<P>
Another draft law seeks to increase the current soft ten
percent value added tax on food, including children's food, to 20
percent.
</P>
<P>
The Russian government is going to motion amendments to the law
on taxation of corporate bodies and individuals to cancel on
January 1 income tax benefits for the military personnel and other
eligible in this category. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
