<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Angolan Constitution to Be Revised </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The draft bill, which was put forward by the ruling party,
Popular Movement for the Liberation of Angola (MPLA), stipulated
that Angola's National Asssembly will master the legislative
power and be authorized to draw up a Constitution.
</P>
<P>
According to the bill, the Drafting Committee will be composed
of 44 parliamentarians, 25 from MPLA, 14 from the main
opposition National Union for the Total Independence of Angola
(UNITA).
</P>
<P>
The other political parties seated in Parliament will share
the rest of the seats.
</P>
<P>
In accordance with the bill, the upcoming draft Constitution
will be proposed by those political parties who have seats in
Parliament and the political party alliance.
</P>
<P>
Those political parties who deserve no places in Parliament,
social organizations as well as civilians who want to make any
propose to amend the constitution can put forward their
suggestions directly to the House Speaker.
</P>
<P>
The Angola's present Constitution was formulated in 1975.
</P>
</TEXT>
