Prime Minister Abdul Salam Majali and Foreign Minister Fayez
Tarawneh on Middle East situation.
</P>
<P>
Before arriving in Amman late Monday evening, Primakov headed
for Syria to meet President Hafez Assad again and presented "new
ideas" from Israeli government on resuming peace talks.
</P>
<P>
He had voiced Russia's willingness to mediate between Syria and
Israel.
</P>
<P>
Primakov's week-long trip in the region began on October 24 in
Lebanon, which also includes Syria, Israel, the Palestinian
self-rule area, Jordan and Egypt.
</P>
<P>
Although Russia co-sponsored the peace process together with
the U.S., its long absence in the region has left Washington
played the dominant role in brokering talks between the Arabs and
Israelis. 
