Museveni left Uganda on October 14, and first went to Senegal
for a four-day official visit. From Senegal he proceeded to Libya
on a three-day official visit at the invitation of the Libyan
government. He then proceeded to the United Kingdom where he
addressed a Commonwealth business forum in London before going to
Edinburgh to attend the four-day Commonwealth heads of state
summit.
</P>
