<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, October 28 (Xinhua) -- European Union (EU)
Commissioner for Foreign Affairs Hans Van Den Broek will arrive
here Thursday to discuss EU-Turkish relations with Turkish
leaders.
</P>
<P>
Van Den Broek is expected to meet with Turkish Parliament
Speaker Hikmet Cetin, Deputy Prime Minister Bulent Ecevit and
Foreign Minister Ismail Cem, according to the Anatolia News
Agency.
</P>
<P>
Turkey's EU membership issue will reportedly be taken up
during the EU official's visit here.
</P>
<P>
Observers here noted that the Turkish government will use
the chance to justify its efforts for full EU membership.
</P>
<P>
Turkish Foreign Ministry officials, who spoke on condition of
anonymity, said that Van Den Broek's visit was planned weeks ago
and had nothing to do with the recent EU ministerial meeting.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the EU meeting held in Mondorf town, Luxembourg
last weekend, German Foreign Minister Klaus Kinkel made it clear
that Bonn cannot support Turkey's EU membership bid at present.
</P>
<P>
He said that Turkey cannot be invited to the accession talks
unless it has made considerable progress on a number of issues,
including the Kurds problem, human rights as well as its
economy.
</P>
<P>
In reaction, Turkish President Suleyman Demirel told a press
conference Monday that Germany should not withdraw its
support for Turkey's EU membership efforts, saying this is also
against Germany's interests.
</P>
<P>
Turkey has been sparing no efforts for full EU membership but
so far no positive results have been achieved owing to its
differences with the European organ. 
</P>
