<HEADLINE> PNA Regards Netanyahu's Policy "Very Dangerous" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, October 28 (Xinhua) -- The Palestinian National
Authority (PNA) today warned that Israeli government's latest
hardline stance on troop redeployment and Jewish settlement is
"very dangerous."
</P>
<P>
The Palestinian news service JMCC today quoted PNA Cabinet
Secretary Ahmed Abdul Rahman as saying Israeli government's
intransigent statement is unacceptable.
</P>
<P>
In his policy address to the Israeli Knesset (Parliament)
Tuesday evening, Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu blamed
the PNA for not doing enough to fight terrorism, thus breaching
its commitments and pledges.
</P>
<P>
He declared that Israeli will continue Jewish settlement
activities in the West Bank and Gaza Strip and refrain from
handing over more land to the PNA unless it fulfills its commitment.
</P>
<P>
