the Palestine Radio saying that the PNA has already contacted
U.S. Peace Envoy Dennis Ross and inquired the U.S. Administration
on the postponement of the talks.
</P>
<P>
Israeli Foreign Minister David Levy refused to go to
Washington for the talks because Netanyahu did not give him clear
instructions governing his negotiations.
</P>
<P>
Netanyahu decided to let the cabinet formulate guidelines and
principles for peace talks during its session on Wednesday.
