<HEADLINE> Seven Hong Kong Young Industrialists Awarded </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 29 (Xinhua) -- Tung Chee Hwa, chief
executive of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR) of
China, presented the Young Industrialists Awards of Hong Kong
today to seven outstanding young entrepreneurs.
</P>
<P>
The awards were given by the Federation of Hong Kong Industries
as a public recognition of the achievements made by the seven
outstanding young industrialists and to encourage them to continue
their contribution to the local industry and the economy of Hong
Kong as a whole.
</P>
<P>
The awards winners -- Ricky Cheng Chung-hing, Choi Yee-sang,
Roy Chung Chi-ping, Benjamin Kwok Chan-yiu, Clement Lam Ching-wah,
Winger Lam Sai-wing and Wilson Wong Wing-shing -- are leaders of
enterprises that engage in high technology and high value-added
industries.
</P>
<P>
This year's award presentation ceremony, the first after Hong
Kong's return to China, coincides with the 10th anniversary of the
awards.
</P>
<P>
Federation Chairman Henry Tang, who himself was given the
awards in 1989, said at the ceremony that he very much enjoys
being an industrialist.
</P>
<P>
He said operating a manufacturing business in Hong Kong
requires determination and long-term vision as challenges come
from every angle.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the chief executive's maiden policy speech
delivered earlier this month, Tang said it had detailed the future
plans and policies of the SAR government to build a solid
foundation for Hong Kong's long-term development as an
international center for industry, finance, trade and services.
</P>
<P>
Tang noted that this year's seven winners are good examples of
success stories. "They demonstrate that if we judge the market
well and correctly identify our niche, we can enjoy value-added
production and prosperity made possible by technology."
</P>
<P>
Tang paid tribute to the awards' sole sponsor, the Sin Hua
Bank, for its continual support for the awards since their
inception, which demonstrates its confidence in the local
industrial sectors.
</P>
<P>
He believed that he himself and the seven awards winners are
also confident about the prospect of industrial development in
Hong Kong. 
