<HEADLINE> Russia Calls for Peaceful Settlement to Dnestr's Status </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, October 29 (Xinhua) -- Chairman of the Russian State
Duma (Lower House) Gennady said today that the status of the
Dnestr region should be settled through negotiations.
</P>
<P>
Moldova can seek various ways to settle the status of the
Dnestr region, such as setting up an autonomous region, republic
or federation, a report from the capital of Moldova Kishinev
quoted Seleznev, who is paying an official visit in Moldova, as
saying.
</P>
<P>
Russia will make an effort to broker negotiations on the
matter, which is an internal issue of Moldova, Seleznev stressed.
</P>
<P>
The separatists in the eastern Dnestr region bordering
southwest Ukraine declared independence in 1990.
</P>
<P>
Hundreds of people were killed when fighting broke out in 1992
between Kishinev and Dnestr's mainly Slav separatists. They were
afraid that with the collapse of the Soviet Union, Moldova might
unite with ethnic kin in neighboring Romania to the west. 
</P>
