<HEADLINE> Hu Jintao Calls for Stronger Grassroots Party Branches </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 29 (Xinhua) -- Senior Communist Party leader
Hu Jintao said today that to strengthen the Party's grassroots
organizations is crucial if the tasks for rural areas put forward
by the Party's 15th National Congress are to be fulfilled.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a national conference on the building of the Party's
grassroots untis in rural areas, Hu, a member of the Standing
Committee of the Political Bureau of the Communist Party of China
(CPC) Central Committee, urged local Party officials to be
clear-minded about the current rural situation and work to improve
grassroots Party organizations in the countryside.
</P>
<P>
Over the past three years, improvements have been made of rural
Party branches. Reviewing work in this regard, Hu said that a
large number of officials who have expertise in rural work have
matured, along with increasing accumulation of experience on Party
building in the rural areas, thus providing good conditions for
further advancement of rural reforms and development.
</P>
<P>
He noted that agriculture is the foundation of the national
economy. Only qualified Party grassroots units in the countryside
can unite farmers around the Party and government, so that the
Party's policies can be implemented well in the rural areas.
</P>
<P>
Further work in this regard must be guided by the theme of the
Party's 15th National Congress, Deng Xiaoping Theory and the rural
policies of the CPC Central Committee, Hu said.
</P>
<P>
The building of rural Party branches should be aimed at
boosting agriculture and rural economy, raising the income of
farmers, and deepening rural reforms, he said.  
</P>
