<HEADLINE> Pricy Art Auction Ends in Chengdu </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, October 29 (Xinhua) -- A diamond and platinum necklace
owned by a French duchess was auctioned for 290,000 yuan, or
nearly 35,000 US dollars, in southwestern Chengdu during the
National Arts Festival.
</P>
<P>
Among the art treasures at the auction, which ended Tuesday
afternoon, were French paintings, sculpture, and other valuable
paintings by well-known Chinese painters such as He Haixia, Qi
Baishi, Xu Beihong, Wu Changshuo, Zhang Daqian and Pan Tianshou.
</P>
<P>
One painting, titled "Birthday Wine God," topped all others
with a selling price of 440,000 yuan (53,000 US dollars). An oil
portrait by Zhang Daqian and Kang Youwei's Chinese calligraphy
were sold on the block for 340,000 yuan and 150,000 yuan.
</P>
<P>
Two bronze sculptures by a famous 19th-century French sculptor
also were up for bidding.
</P>
<P>
More than 75 percent of the 234 auctioned items were sold, with
a total business volume of 4.76 million yuan (573,500 US dollars),
said the auction organizers.
</P>
<P>
Some foreign works of art made their debut in Chengdu, capital
of Sichuan Province, the organizers added. 
