<HEADLINE> Interest of Housing Mortgage Loans Down in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 29 (Xinhua) -- Beijing Branch of the China
Construction Bank has adjusted the interest of housing mortgage
loans to give more incentive to individual buyers in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Following the drop of overall interest issued by the central
bank last week, the branch has lowered the interest rates of
housing mortgage loans by 1.62 percentage points for one to five
years, 1.8 percentage points for five to 10 years, and 1.89
percentage points for above 10 years.
</P>
<P>
The branch started offering such loans, which can allow a
maximum of 70 percent of the housing price, to Beijing residents
this past September.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that the volume of individual housing purchase
rose by more than 40 percent in the first three quarters of this
year. Nearly half of the housing sold in Beijing went as
individually-owned property.  
</P>
