<DOCNO> XIE19971029.0091 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> State Councilor Urges to Boost Software Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, October 29 (Xinhua) -- China should speed up the
development of its software industry and make the work one of the
most imperative cross-century goals.
</P>
<P>
State Councilor Song Jian, who is also minister-in-charge of
the State Science and Technology Commission, made the suggestion
at today's closing of a three-day national discussion panel on the
software industry.
</P>
<P>
Over 300 participants from across the country attended the
meeting, which was sponsored by central government departments.
</P>
<P>
In his speech, Song pledged to develop the software industry
rapidly, so as to turn it into a pillar industry of the country in
the early years of the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
He also said that the country should step up macro-guidance
over the software sector, build software production bases, unify
the standards, safeguard the property rights, work out correct
industrial policies and preferential policies, set up and develop
powerful and active enterprises, explore the market and foster
talented workers.
</P>
<P>
The software industry should be opened up and conduct exchanges
with the outside world in areas of information, materials and
personnel, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
