<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Guangxi Launches New Expressway Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIHAI, October 29 (Xinhua) -- The Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous
Region today started to build a new expressway from Qinzhou to
Beihai.
</P>
<P>
The new expressway, which will have a speed limit of 120 km,
cost 2.1 billion yuan and is scheduled to be completed by 1999.
</P>
<P>
The project is part of a national trunk road extending from
Chongqing, the country's fourth municipality, and Beihai, a
coastal open city in the southernmost part of Guangxi.
</P>
<P>
When completed, the road will connect with the just-built
expressway between Qinzhou and Fangcheng Port, a port city in
Guangxi. By then, a coastal expressway network will have taken
shape in the autonomous region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
