<HEADLINE> German Shares Rebound </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, October 29 (Xinhua) -- German share values rose sharply in
trading today, reacting to an overnight dramatic rebound in Wall
Street followed by strong recovery on Far Eastern exchanges.
</P>
<P>
In Frankfurt, the main 30-share DAX index reached 3778.89 points by
noontime in an across-the-board recovery, up 211.67 points from last
day's closing of 3,567.22 points.
</P>
<P>
The rebound partly recovered the heavy losses Tuesday, when German
share values plunged 8.04 percent.  
