<HEADLINE> Becker Makes Full Schedule for Next Season </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, October 29 (Xinhua) -- Semi-retired Boris Becker
admitted that he had planned a full schedule for the first three
months of next season.
</P>
<P>
The German tennis hero will start his season in Dubai and play
a few indoor tournaments after that. Scottsdale, Key Biscayne and
maybe Indian Wells are also to be taken into account.
</P>
<P>
The former world No.1 player will face Pete Sampras, current
top player in the world, in the second round of the Paris Indoor
Open Wednesday, after he ousted Australian Mark Woodforde 6-2, 6-4
on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The triple Wimbledon champion announced this summer his
quitting in next year's Wimbledon tournament when he was upset by
Sampras. Becker said he was almost sure of his last appearance of
the Open in Paris.
</P>
<P>
Becker has won 49 singles titles during his career, containing
1985, 1986 and 1989 Wimbledon triumphs, 1991 and 1996 Australian
Opens wins and a United States Open champion in 1990. 
</P>
