attend the Commonwealth summit in Britain, Mandela held talks with
Gaddafi last Wednesday night on ways of developing bilateral ties
and a number of regional issues.
</P>
<P>
The agency added that Gaddafi and Mandela will hold talks to
examine developments of the Lockerbie issue involving Libya, and
the U.S. and Britain.
</P>
<P>
The U.N. Security Council imposed an air ban on Libya in 1992
to force the surrender of two Libyans wanted in the 1988 bombing
of Pan AM flight 103 over Lockerbie, Scotland, which killed 270
people. 
