<HEADLINE> Shanghai, HK Scholars Discuss Issues on Education </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 29 (Xinhua) -- A symposium on Shanghai and
Hong Kong's education development and cooperation opened here
today to promote education exchanges between the two cities.
</P>
<P>
The symposium, jointly sponsored by the Chinese University of
Hong Kong, HK Education Research Institute, Shanghai Education
Society and East China Teachers University, has received more than
60 papers which explored the educational histories and theories,
reforms on curriculum, teaching methods and education system in
the two areas, as well as other issues.
</P>
<P>
