<HEADLINE> Japan to Help Indonesia Stabilize Currency </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, October 29 (Xinhua) -- Japanese Prime Minister Ryutaro
Hashimoto today offered to provide financial aid to help Indonesia
stabilize its beleaguered currency, the rupiah, Kyoto News
reported.
</P>
<P>
Hashimoto made the offer in a telephone conversation with
Indonesian president Soeharto.
</P>
<P>
Japan is ready to provide funds if the International Monetary
Fund (IMF) and Indonesia reach agreement on an IMF-backed economic
and financial program to help restore confidence to the rupiah and
stabilize Indonesia's economy, Hashimoto was quoted as telling
Soeharto.
</P>
<P>
Hashimoto gave the assurance on ways to defend the Indonesian
currency against sustained speculative attacks, which has sliced
more than a third off the value of the rupiah in recent months and
triggered a crisis of investor confidence. 
</P>
