<HEADLINE> Stationery Trade Fair in HK Attracts World Exhibitors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 29 (Xinhua) -- More than 100 exhibitors from
17 countries and regions are displaying their
writing equipment and paper products at an international trade
fair opened today at the Hong Kong Convention and Exhibition
Center.
</P>
<P>
The International Trade Fair for Stationery, Office Supplies
and Educational Systems (Pen &AMP; Paper), which runs until October
31, has attracted 107 exhibitors from Hong Kong, China's mainland,
France, Germany, Hungary, India, Italy, Malaysia, Pakistan, the
Philippines, South Korea, Spain, Switzerland, Taiwan, the United
Kingdom, the United States and Vietnam.
</P>
<P>
The fair, organized by the Hong Kong Trade Development Council
(HKTDC) and the German company of Messe Frankfurt (HK), features
an extensive array of latest products in five categories: writing
equipment, paper and paper products, office supplies, artist
equipment, and educational equipment.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the opening ceremony of the fair, HKTDC's Executive
Director Michael Sze noted that while Asian economies are growing
at impressive rates, incomes are rising and demand for more
sophisticated products, like stationery, is rising as well.
</P>
<P>
"Asia's growth is also fueling demand for upgraded office
supplies and up to date business systems. And in the West, demand
is also up due to an expanding home office market, particularly in
the United States," Sze said.
</P>
<P>
He said that the fair not only strongly reconfirms Hong Kong's
status as the trade fair capital of the region but also
strengthens Hong Kong's position as the regional center for the
industry.  
</P>
</TEXT>
