<HEADLINE> Putonghua Learners Increase in Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Lei Heong Iok, vice-president of the Macao Institute of Science
and Technology which undertakes the Chinese language training of
civil servants, said on Tuesday at a ceremony on the issuing of
three volume of new Putonghua textbooks that learning Putonghua
has become a fashion among Macao civil servants now.
</P>
<P>
There were 1,920 Putonghua learners in 1996 at the institute,
and the number rose to 2,450 this year, up 27.6 percent, said Lei.
</P>
<P>
About 10,000 out the total 18,000 Macao civil servants have
received some kind of training in Putonghua since 1987.
</P>
<P>
The learners include both those of Chinese origin, the
Macao-born Portuguese servants, and those from Portugal who have
decided to stay on after 1999.
</P>
<P>
When they finish the Putonghua training course at the institute
after learning all nine volumes of textbooks, they will be at
about the same level as senior middle school graduates in China's
inland, Lei said.
</P>
<P>
The first four volumes of the textbooks have been published by
the institute in cooperation with the Department of Administration
and Personnel. The remaining will be published soon.  
</P>
</TEXT>
