<HEADLINE> Mozambian Newspaper Condemned Coup Attempt in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, October 29 (Xinhua) -- Mozambique's newspaper,
Noticias, in a commentary today, condemned the attempted coup
in Zambia, saying that violence should never be taken as means
to solve pressing problems in Zambia.
</P>
<P>
The commentary said that the short-fated coup in
Lusaka Tuesday is "worrisome to not only Zambia, but the southern
African nations as a whole".
</P>
<P>
It said that though Zambian President Frederick Chiluba has
been under strong criticism from the opposition at home, violence
should not be taken in solving their differences, since violence begets
violence.
</P>
<P>
The failled military coup in Zambia, like a potential virus,
will directly threaten the stability in Southern African region,
the commentary said.
</P>
<P>
It said, "People should not take the attempted coup in Zambia
as a sheer internal issue, governments in southern African
nations should reflect on it."
</P>
<P>
In the past few months, stability in the southern African
region had been endangered by the civil war in former Zaire, it
said.
</P>
<P>
" We hold that conflict should be solved through dialogue. We
don't stand for violence, much less foreign interference which
often conveys an expansionist desire," the commentary noted.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Mozambican President Joaquim Chissano in a
statement Tuesday, also denounce the attempted coup in Zambia.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
