<HEADLINE> Kazakhstan, Russia Strengthen Military Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALMA-ATA, October 29 (Xinhua) -- Kazakh President Nursultan
Nazarbayev said strengthened military cooperation between
Kazakhstan and Russia would serve the interests of both countries
and also improve security in Central Asia.
</P>
<P>
After a meeting here today with Nazarbayev, Russian Defense
Minister Igor Sergeyev told reporters the two countries would
further bilateral military cooperation and strengthen security in
Central Asia.
</P>
<P>
He added that Kazakhstan and Russia would carry out joint
military exercises next year.
</P>
<P>
Sergeyev, who arrived here Tuesday for a visit to Kazakhstan,
also spoke with Kazakh Defense Minister Mukhtar Altynbayev during
which time Russia agreed to provide aid to Kazakhstan in military
education and to help it resume the academy of military sciences.
</P>
<P>
The two sides agreed that the military departments of the two
countries would strengthen ecological protection.
</P>
<P>
They also discussed the Kazakh purchase of Russian weapons and
Russia's lease on the Kazakh weapons' testing ground.
</P>
<P>
Sergeyev added that Russia would provide four SU-27 fighters
for Kazakhstan by the end of this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
