<HEADLINE> Gobert Sacked on Doping </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, October 29 (Xinhua) -- Anthony Gobert of Australia
was sacked by Suzuki for drug-taking before the motorcycle racer
was to ride in the world 500cc championships on the United States
Superbike Circuit.
</P>
<P>
But the International Motorcycle Federation (FIM) has not
admitted the results of Suzuki's team-ordered drug test and no ban
of the Australian was announced, reports from Sydney said
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Gobert's mother and manager Sue Gobert said the test was
illegal because full precautions required by FIM were not taken.
</P>
<P>
The Goberts claimed to take legal action against the company's
sacking while the son would head to Vance and Hines team. 
</P>
