<HEADLINE> India to Speed Up Clearance of Import Cargo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, October 29 (Xinhua) -- The Indian government has
decided to simplify the procedures to clear import cargo as part
of its efforts to boost the sluggish economy, the local press said
today.
</P>
<P>
Import cargo will be cleared within two days instead of the
prevailing time frame of 21 days starting December 1, Industry
Secretary R. Prasad told at a meeting of industrialists here
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Assuring the industry that it should not unduly worry about the
industrial slowdown, Prasad said the Indian economy is poised to
grow at 6 percent and industry can attain double digit growth in
the fiscal year of 1997-98 (from April 1997 to March 1998).
</P>
<P>
"There will be a significant upturn in the economy in the next
six to nine months and it will last," the industry secretary said,
but he cautioned the Indian industry against attaching too much
attention to statistics and predicting a gloomy picture. 
</P>
</TEXT>
