<HEADLINE> Macao Gold Shops See Booming Business </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, October 29 (Xinhua) -- Macao gold shops have witnessed a
booming business over the past few days as the price of gold hit a
12-year low across the world.
</P>
<P>
Local gold shops have reported a business growth of from 30 to
60 percent over normal days as the shops were overcrowded with
customers.
</P>
<P>
The price of gold in Macao dropped to the lowest in 10 years
last Saturday after it plummeted on international markets
following the news that Switzerland plans to sell 1,400 tons of
reserved gold.
</P>
<P>
However, experts said that the crash of stock markets worldwide
has pushed some investors to divert their money to the gold
market, noting that the price of gold has bounced back a little
bit. 
</P>
</TEXT>
