<HEADLINE> Leading Criminal of Robbery Case Sentenced in Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, October 29 (Xinhua) -- A leading member of the gang that
robbed 10 million Hong Kong dollars (about 1.29 million U.S.
dollars) in 1995 was sentenced to 18 and half years imprisonment
and fines by a Macao court.
</P>
<P>
The Macao Daily News reported that Chan Kwai Ching, 39, pleaded
guilty of pirate and robbery, was sentenced to 18 and half years
behind bars and a fine of 17,400 patacas (about 2202.5 U.S.
dollars) on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Chan and others conspired and hijacked a Hong-Kong bound ferry
boat in June 1995 and robbed 10 million Hong Kong dollars which a
local bank was shipping to Hong Kong, the report said.
</P>
<P>
While most other suspects of the case have been caught and
convicted in Hong Kong, China's inland and Macao, Chan remained at
large until he was rejected entry by Taiwan authorities last year
and caught by Macao police.  
</P>
</TEXT>
