<HEADLINE> Chinese Journalist Finishes His Olympic Tour </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, October 29 (Xinhua) -- Chinese sports journalist Bu
Fanzhou completed a 15,000 km bicycle journey in front of the
Sydney Opera House Wednesday after visiting each of the 21 host
cities of the Summer Olympics.
</P>
<P>
Bu, a journalist for the China Sports magazine since 1985,
finished his 16 month journey in Sydney, Australia, the city that
will host the first Olympic Games in the new millennium.
</P>
<P>
In front of the opera house, the 39 year old journalist was met
by John Coates, president of the Australian Olympic Committee,
Phil Coles, member of the International Olympic Committee, and Hua
Junduo, Chinese Ambassador to Australia.
</P>
<P>
His mission was to experience both mentally and physically what
the Olympic spirit entails. He diarised his experience and taken
about 20,000 pictures.
</P>
<P>
Bu, a graduate from Beijing University, traveled through 17
countries on four continents, including Greece, the United States,
Japan, South Korea, Spain, Italy, Germany, the Netherlands,
Belgium, France, Britain, Sweden, Finland, Russia, Canada and
Mexico. 
</P>
