<HEADLINE> Nigeria to Launch International TV Service </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, October 29 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria will start 24-hour
satellite television broadcast to all parts of the world from
November 3 this year, according to press reports today.
</P>
<P>
The signals of the new station, African Independent Television
(AIT) International, will be beamed to the African continent,
Europe, the Carribeans, the United States and Asia through one of
the newest satellites recently launched by the International
Telecommunications Satellite Organization.
</P>
<P>
The station, run by DAAR Communications Ltd in Lagos, will
broadcast initially in English but later widen its audience with
the introduction of French, Spanish, Portuguese, Swahili and
Hausa language programs, company chairman Raymond Dokpesi said on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
This is Nigeria's first worldwide television broadcast and the
head of state, General Sani Abacha, is expected to commission the
23-million-U.S. dollar project.  
</P>
</TEXT>
