<HEADLINE> Beijing Hosts International Computer Conference </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 29 (Xinhua) -- The '97 Hong Kong-Beijing
International Computer Conference, sponsored by the China Computer
Federation and Hong Kong Computer Society, opened today in the
Chinese capital.
</P>
<P>
The two organizations have sponsored four similar conferences
since 1994. The ongoing conference is the first to be held here
since China resumed sovereignty over Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Representatives from more than 250 companies at home and
abroad, including major names such as IBM, Oracle and Legend, will
discuss the latest developments in information technology, the
effect of the information age on society, and China's development
strategy for the information industry.
</P>
<P>
The two-day conference is based on the theme "Information is
Power." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
