<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar Up More Than One US Cent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, October 29 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar scooted
up to close more than one U.S. cent stronger today in Sydney,
following a stunning comeback on the local stock exchange.
</P>
<P>
The local unit finished here at 70.57 U.S. cents, from 69.29
U.S. cents Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
But it was off a high for the day of 71.50 U.S. cents after
profit-takers moved in during late session dealings.
</P>
<P>
John Basile, Colonial State Bank foreign exchange market head,
said the recovery in U.S. and local stock prices, stronger gold
and stop loss buying overnight had all combined to help the
previously fading currency.
</P>
<P>
Basile said although trading was steadier today, financial
markets still fear global and Australian equity markets could
still be in for a rocky ride.
</P>
<P>
The local unit was at 84.04 Japanese yen, from 83.58, and at
1.2286 German marks, from 1.1959. 
</P>
</TEXT>
