<HEADLINE> Beijing Hosts International Conference on Intelligent Systems </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 29 (Xinhua) -- The International Conference on
Intelligent Systems, sponsored by the U.S.-based Institute of
Electrical and Electronics Engineers (IEEE), opened here today.
</P>
<P>
The conference will cover almost all fields related to computer
intelligence. Discussions will cover fuzzy logic, expert systems,
robotics and their applications, pattern processing, intellectual
communication networks and the application of multi-media.
</P>
<P>
The IEEE is one of the most authoritative international
academic organizations in high-technology fields.
</P>
<P>
China has an important role in computer intelligence and its
industrial application, said an IEEE official as the reason for
holding the meeting in Beijing. China's rapid economic growth
offers a potential market for computer intelligence technology in
industrial development, the official said.
</P>
<P>
More than 100 overseas experts from the U.S., Australia, Japan,
Germany, Singapore, Britain and more than 200 domestic scholars
attended the conference.
</P>
<P>
More than 700 academic papers from home and abroad were
presented at the conference. 
</P>
</TEXT>
