<HEADLINE> Tokyo Stocks Rebound Sharply on Rally in New York </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, October 29 (Xinhua) -- Tokyo stocks rebounded sharply
following the largest single-day rise on Wall Street.
</P>
<P>
The key Nikkei average of 225 selected issues on the First
Section of the Tokyo Stock Exchange, which plunged 725.67 points
on Tuesday, rose 544.35 points, or 3.34 percent to close at
16,857.04.
</P>
<P>
The broader-based Tokyo Stock Price Index, covering all issues
on the First Section, increased 43.68 points or 3.46 percent to
1,306.79.
</P>
<P>
Turnover on the First Section came to an estimated 450 million
shares, up from Tuesday's 403.21 million shares.
</P>
<P>
The Tokyo market reacted briskly to the largest-ever point gain
Tuesday on the New York market where the 30-issue Dow Jones
Industrial Average jumped 337.17 points following the previous
day's plunge.
</P>
<P>
The bullish recovery in New York has diminished growing concern
over the chain reaction of plunges in the global stock markets,
traders said.
</P>
<P>
On the Tokyo Foreign Exchange, the U.S. dollar was fettered in
a narrow range at the 120 level. It was changing hands at
120.35-38 Japanese yen at 5 o'clock in the afternoon. 
</P>
</TEXT>
