<HEADLINE> Hun Sen Meets Khmer Rouge Leader </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, October 29 (Xinhua) -- Cambodian Second Prime
Minister Hun Sen held talks earlier today with former Khmer Rouge
leader Ieng Sary, but the details of the talks were not disclosed.
</P>
<P>
The meeting took place at Hun Sen's suburban villa.
</P>
<P>
Ieng Sary, who did not take sides in Cambodia's recent
political turmoil, arrived here on Tuesday for the first time
since the Khmer Rouge was driven from power by a Vietnamese
invasion in early 1979.
</P>
<P>
The Cambodian co-prime minister met this morning with Ieng Sary
and they had lunch together afterwards. Ieng Sary is expected to
hold a press conference the following morning to brief on the
talks, it was reported.
</P>
<P>
Pardoned by king Norodom Sihanouk in September last year, Ieng
Sary was former foreign minister under the 1975-1979 Khmer Rouge
regime.
</P>
<P>
Ieng Sary with several thousand Khmer Rouge forces broke away
from the guerrilla movement and crossed over to the government of
Cambodia in August last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
