<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-29 10:18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kuwait Stock Market Drops But Shielded Against </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, October 29 (Xinhua) -- The Kuwaiti stock market
dropped by 2.5 percent in the world big markets turmoil Tuesday,
but local market analysts said today it would be shielded from
market crisis.
</P>
<P>
Local newspapers, both English and Arabic, quoted the
analysts as believing that international crisis might provide a
good opportunity to buy up undervalued stocks and cool down
buying of the overvalued shares in the market which were seen
roaring recently.
</P>
<P>
They said Kuwait is well insulated from the international
crisis and the crisis would not have a big effect on its market.
</P>
<P>
The drop was mainly caused by psychological elements without
any specific reason, they said adding that this is a healthy
correction.
</P>
<P>
In the wake of the disastrous performance of major stock
markets in the last two days, the Kuwait Stock Exchange closed
70.4 points lower than Monday at 2707.1 points, dropping from the
highest 2777.5 point since last year.
</P>
<P>
Investment companies were some of the hardest hit in
yesterday's drop because of concerns about their exposure to
stocks in the foreign markets where shares have spiraled
downwards.
</P>
<P>
The analysts argued that Kuwait's foreign investments are
focused mainly on the European and the US markets, which they
expect to recover soon.
</P>
<P>
They also do not expect a massive capital withdrawal from
foreign markets at present.
</P>
<P>
Kuwaiti stock market has been rising strongly for the past two
years, the index had been up 45.76 percent this year following a
40 percent increase in 1996. Yesterday's index was still 42
percent higher then that starting 1997.
</P>
<P>
Despite the drop, volume, value and number of deals increased
by 7.2 percent, 9.8 percent and 2 percent respectively, according
to a market statement.
</P>
<P>
However, other experts believe that the selling pressure
experienced by the Kuwaiti stock market could continue for a
couple of days. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
