<HEADLINE> NPC Chairman Meets Singaporean Deputy PM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 29 (Xinhua) -- Qiao Shi, chairman of the
Standing Committee of China's National People's Congress, said
here today that the development of friendship and cooperation
between China and Singapore is conducive to peace and stability in
the region.
</P>
<P>
He expressed firm belief that Sino-Singaporean friendship and
cooperation in various fields will be strengthened in the future.
</P>
<P>
Qiao made the remarks during an afternoon meeting with
Singaporean Deputy Prime Minister and Defense Minister Tan Keng
Yam and his party. Tan Keng Yam is in China on his first official
visit.
</P>
<P>
Noting that the Singaporean guests will visit the Suzhou
Industrial Park, Qiao pointed out that both governments have
strongly supported the park, a symbol of bilateral friendship.
</P>
<P>
Qiao said Tan's visit will further promote the growth of
friendship and cooperation between the two countries, the two
peoples and their armed forces.
</P>
<P>
Tan said that Singapore and China have enjoyed friendly
relations for many years, with the two sides engaging in smooth
political, economic, social and cultural cooperation.
</P>
<P>
He said the two countries are currently cooperating in defense
areas, and noted that friendly bilateral cooperation is conducive
to economic construction and improving the lives of people in
countries throughout the region.
</P>
<P>
General Chi Haotian, vice-chairman of China's Central Military
Commission, state councillor and defence minister, attended the
meeting.  
</P>
</TEXT>
