<HEADLINE> Share Prices Recover on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, October 29 (Xinhua) -- Share prices rallied and
recovered some ground lost Tuesday, as the benchmark Straits Times
Industrials Index bounced back by 44.36 points to close at
1,541.39 today.
</P>
<P>
Total market volume stood at 287.41 million units, worth 525.63
million Singapore dollars (about 332.68 million U.S. dollars).
Advances overtook declines 270 to 107, while 229 other counters
remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong Land was the most actively traded stock as it
registered a turnover of 19.41 million units. It was followed by
Land &AMP; Gen which had 12.36 million shares traded. Local computer
maker IPC Corporation was next with 10.25 million shares changed
hands.
</P>
<P>
Local computer sound card maker Creative 50 led the gainers of
the day as it rose 4.2 dollars to finish at 39.9 Singapore
dollars. The Singapore Press Holdings (SPH) Foreign increased 4.1
dollars to end at 21.8 Singapore dollars, while Development Bank
of Singapore (DBS) Foreign gained 2.2 dollars to close at 13.3
Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Perlis Plant was the biggest loser as it
declined 68 cents to end at 2.58 dollars. ICB fell 30 cents to
close at four dollars, and Jurong Engineering Warrant0207 dropped
25 cents to finish at 0.45 dollar.  
</P>
</TEXT>
