<HEADLINE> French PM Meets With Chinese Guest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, October 29 (Xinhua) -- French Prime Minister Lionel
Jospin met Tuesday with Wen Jiabao, member of the Political Bureau
of the Central Committee of the Chinese Communist Party, who was
on a week-long visit to France.
</P>
<P>
Jospin said that he was glad and honored to meet Wen, who was
the first important Chinese guest he received since he became
prime minister in June.
</P>
<P>
Jospin said that as President Jacques Chirac had wished, France
and China could expand cooperation and exchange in the economic
field, as well as increase political cooperation in major
international affairs.
</P>
<P>
Both France and China support the establishment of a multipolar
world structure, and oppose domination by one single country in
the world, Jospin noted.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed his satisfaction over the cooperation between
France and China in the agricultural field, and said that small
and medium-sized enterprises of the two countries can enhance
their cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Wen said that the main purpose of his visit was to visit the
agricultural and industrial institutions of France, and to discuss
with French friends the promotion of cooperation in the
agricultural field between China and France.
</P>
<P>
He said that China highly valued its relations with France, and
expressed satisfaction over cooperation in agricultural and other
economic fields between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Wen held talks with French Minister of Agriculture and Fishing
Louis Le Pensec on Monday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
