sale of the book by Andre Rougeot and Jean-Michel Verne,
"L'Affaire Yann Piat, Des Assassins au Coeur du Pouvoir (Yann Piat
Affair, Assassins in the Heart of Power)," after a court ordered
the suppression of about 15 passages in which former defense
minister and president of the Union for French Democracy, Francois
Leotard, was implicitly accused of ordering the murder of Yann
Piat, a mafia-fighter murdered in 1992. 
