<HEADLINE> State Councillor Meets Brazilian Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 29 (Xinhua) -- Chinese State Councillor Li
Guixian met with a delegation from the Ministry of Social Welfare
of Brazil led by Minister Reinhold Stephanes here today.
</P>
<P>
Li noted that bilateral relations have been growing smoothly
since the two countries set up diplomatic ties. He told the
visitors that Brazil's experience in social welfare is worth
learning from by China.
</P>
<P>
He also noted that relevant departments of the governments of
the two countries have carried out effective cooperation in the
past years. He said that China is ready to strengthen its
cooperation with Brazil in the field of social welfare.
</P>
<P>
Stephanes said that the Brazilian government places great
importance on developing its relations with China. He hopes that
the two countries will step up cooperation in all fields.
</P>
<P>
The Brazilian delegation is here as guest of the Chinese
Ministry of Civil Affairs.  
