<HEADLINE> Speculative Trading Pushes Karachi Stock Index Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, October 29 (Xinhua) -- Speculative trading took the
reigns of shares at Karachi Stock Exchange (KSE) today as the
KSE-100 index crossed the 1800 barrier.
</P>
<P>
The KSE-100 Index was up 40.79 points to 1837 at the close of
first session.
</P>
<P>
Dealers attributed the positive trend at KSE to bullish
activity in other bourses of the world.
</P>
<P>
In the early morning the index saw a surge of almost 70 points.
</P>
<P>
The stock market Tuesday virtually crashed as a result of what
analysts called a fallout of the global turmoil in major bourses,
plunging the KSE-100 index by a record 171.26 points at 1,788.33
or about 9 percent on panic liquidation coming from all quarters.
</P>
<P>
Trading had to be suspended in the afternoon session before the
closing bell to apparently forestall fresh sell-off.  
</P>
</TEXT>
