<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Clothing Becomes Leading Export in East China Port City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NINGBO, October 29 (Xinhua) -- Clothing has become not only the
leading export in Ningbo, a port city in Zhejiang Province, but
also in all of China.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that the city exported 382 million U.S. dollars
in clothing through September 1997, a 10 percent increase over the
same period last year. The figure ranks first in the country and
accounts for 18.86 percent of the city's total.
</P>
<P>
The city has rapidly increased exports since 1988. Last year,
exports exceeded 503 million U.S. dollars, 180 times the 1988
figure. The annual growth rate for clothing exports was 81.58
percent, 30.36 percentage points more than the city's average for
other industries.
</P>
<P>
The city's clothing products, mainly knitwear, now go to 74
countries and regions. Asia is the largest market with 60 percent
of the total exports followed by Europe, North America and Oceania.
</P>
<P>
Many clothing enterprises, including joint ventures and
overseas-funded firms, have become direct exporters.
</P>
<P>
A group of clothing enterprises with well-known Chinese brands
such as Youngor and Shanshan have exported more than 3 million
U.S. dollars each.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
