<HEADLINE> HK Stocks Close 18.82 Percent Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 29 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's stocks surged
18.8 percent today, with the key Hang Seng index closing up
1,705.41 points, wiping out all of Tuesday's devastating losses.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng blue-chip index ended today's session at
10,765.30 points, its biggest gain in both points and percentage
terms. The powerful rally reversed Tuesday's plunge of 1,438.31
points, or 13.70 percent, its biggest point loss ever.
</P>
<P>
This recovery came at the opening this morning in the wake of
the biggest one-day gain ever on Wall Street overnight. The Hang
Seng index surged 17.3 percent at the opening today, with the key
Hang Seng Index leaping 1,570.24 points to 10,630.13 in the first
two minutes of trade, and rose 1,512.42 points, or 16.69 percent,
to close at 10,572.31 at midday.
</P>
<P>
Today's market performance has enhanced hopes that the market
is bottoming out.  
</P>
