<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Inner Mongolian Chorus to Attend European Choral Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HOHHOT, October 29 (Xinhua) -- A chorus of 40 young Mongolian
vocalists left for Spain on Tuesday to attend the European Choral
Festival.
</P>
<P>
The chorus will represent China in the choral contest to be
held in the northern Spanish city of Tolosa.
</P>
<P>
Mongolians, many of whom settled in north China, are known for
their sonorous and resonant singing which is believed to be a gift
of nomadic life on boundless stretches of grasslands.
</P>
<P>
The Mongolian chorus, established seven years ago, has
delighted audiences in dozens of countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
The chorus, known as a "fresh flower" of the Inner Mongolia
Autonomous Region, won high praise from experts during the Fourth
World Choral Festival held last year in Sydney.
</P>
<P>
The chorus, which will perform in both Mongolian and standard
Chinese, will also present a number of special concerts during its
stay in Spain. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
