<HEADLINE> Philippine Military Ready Against Rebel Attacks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, October 29 (Xinhua) -- Chief of Staff of the Philippine
Armed Forces Arnulfo Acedera said today that the military is ready
to react to any major attacks to be launched by the rebel groups.
</P>
<P>
Acedera said this in response to reports that some Moro Islamic
Liberation Front (MILF) extremists held a secret meeting with
another rebel group last month to plan a strategy against the
military.
</P>
<P>
Although the government troops withdrew from their previous
positions in line with the July 16 ceasefire agreement with the
MILF, some units are still operating in the area to respond to any
attacks, he said.
</P>
<P>
Acedera said he had directed all military units to take
security measures to avert any surprise attacks after capturing
two top leaders of the Alex Boncayao Brigade rebel group.
</P>
<P>
He added that the military has no intention to release the two
rebel leaders.
</P>
<P>
However, Al Hadj Murad, MILF vice chairman for military
affairs, downplayed the secret meeting, saying it was only "sort
of exchange of ideas along the lower level of the two groups".
</P>
<P>
The MILF is a 12,000-member rebel group in the country. It
entered a peace process with the government early this year, but
so far made little progress in forging a peace agreement with the
government. 
</P>
</TEXT>
