<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Xiaolangdi Project Operates Smoothly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAOLANGDI (Yellow River), October 29 (Xinhua) -- The
Xiaolangdi Multi-Purpose Water Control Project has operated
normally since yesterday's closure of a cofferdam on the Yellow
River.
</P>
<P>
Water from the main channel was diverted through an underground
diversion tunnel and surged toward an energy-consumption pool,
then reentered the river downstream.
</P>
<P>
Only one of three diversion tunnels is operating during the
current dry season, a period in which the flow rate is a mere one
hundredth of the rate during peak flood season, according to a
project official.
</P>
<P>
A downstream cofferdam will be closed in the near future. Water
trapped between the two cofferdams will be pumped out and
construction of the 154-meter dam will begin. 
</P>
</TEXT>
