<BODY>
<HEADLINE> University In East China Increases Dunhuang Research </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, October 29 (Xinhua) -- East China's Hangzhou
University, in the capital of Zhejiang Province, has gotten its
first two postgraduates working for a master's degree on the
Dunhuang Mogao Grottoes.
</P>
<P>
The two students are from Sichuan and Zhejiang provinces. They
are majoring in Dunhuang documents and philology and mean an
increase in the university's work in this field.
</P>
<P>
The university has decided to put more into Dunhuang research,
according to Prof. Huang Zheng, the 39-year-old director of the
university's Dunhuang Research Center. At present, only Lanzhou
University, Northwest Normal University, and Sichuan United
University have graduate studies on Dunhuang.
</P>
<P>
Hangzhou University started courses on Dunhuang culture and
documents recently, and has about 50 students enrolled every
year. It has actually had some well-known Dunhuang experts like
Jiang Liangfu, Jiang Lihong, and Guo Zaiyi, since the 1950s.
</P>
<P>
One of those students, Yu Xin, submitted his thesis to the 1997
International Symposium on Dunhuang Research, held in Hangzhou
recently. 
</P>
</TEXT>
