<HEADLINE> China Develops International Art Exchanges </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, October 29 (Xinhua) -- China is preparing to sponsor
an art Festival in Russia, an art exhibition in the Republic of
Korea (ROK), and the '98 International Arts Festival at home.
</P>
<P>
According to a Ministry of Culture representative attending
the ongoing Fifth China Art Festival in Chengdu, a 150-member
Chinese delegation of dancers, musicians, acrobats and opera
artists will perform at the China Art Festival in Russia at the
end of October.
</P>
<P>
The festival will also feature a Chinese film week and
exhibitions of traditional Chinese paintings and photos.
</P>
<P>
An art exhibition in December will introduce ancient Chinese
cultural relics and contemporary handicrafts to people of the ROK.
</P>
<P>
The Fifth China Art Festival has provided a stage for
Chinese and overseas artists to perform together and exchange
ideas on different forms of arts.
</P>
<P>
China has signed cultural and art exchange accords with 137
countries, and more than 10,000 Chinese artists have participated
in exchange activities.  
</P>
