<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tibetan Buddhism Undergoing Resurgence (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, October 29 (Xinhua) -- Freedom in religious belief is
guaranteed in the Tibet Autonomous Region, and Tibetan Buddhism is
in the prime of life, a noted Tibetan scholar says.
</P>
<P>
According to Gabsang Gya, an assistant research fellow in the
Institute of World Religions of the Chinese Academy of Social
Sciences, the policy of freedom in religious belief has fully been
implemented in Tibet.
</P>
<P>
To meet the needs of religious people, the central and local
government have spent more than 300 million yuan (36 million US
dollars) in the past decade on renovating Tibetan monasteries, and
many, like the Potala Palace and the Johkang, Zhebung, Sera,
Sagya, Samyai and Gandain monasteries, have been rebuilt or are
undergoing renovations, the scholar says.
</P>
<P>
There are 1,787 religious sites in Tibet, 300 more than in 1951
when Tibet was liberated, and all of them are open all the year round.
</P>
<P>
Thanks to the restoration work after the destruction of the
Great Cultural Revolution (1966-76), there are 46,380 monks and
nuns living in monasteries, where they are free to hold religious
activities.
</P>
<P>
In his study of conditions across Tibet, the scholar found that
major religious festivals, some of which were seldom seen before,
have been restored, and many are done on a larger scale.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971029.0184 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Foreign Tourists Flock to the "City of Gardens" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, October 29 (Xinhua) -- Suzhou, widely known as the
"City of Chinese Gardens", hosted over 300,000 overseas tourists
in the first nine months of this year, up 17 percent on the 1996
period.
</P>
<P>
The city, which is located near Shanghai, expects to fulfill
its annual targets of 370,000 overseas tourists and 100 million US
dollars tourism earnings, according to a city tourism official.
</P>
<P>
The official attributed the growth to the development of new
tourist programs and active overseas promotions.
</P>
<P>
Tourists are not only attracted by world-class attractions and
numerous gardens, including the Humble Administrator's Garden,
Hanshan Temple and the Huqiu Pagoda, but also by new itineraries
such as the ancient town tour, Taihu Lake tour, and folklore and
country tours. The International Silk Festival held in September
was also a major success.
</P>
<P>
Local travel agencies have also achieved notable results from
promotional campaigns in Japan, South Asia, Europe and the United
States.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
