<DOCNO> XIE19971029.0185 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Four Southeast Asian Games Medalists Tested Positive </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, October 29 (Xinhua) -- Organizers of Southeast Asian
Games said four medalist at this month's Games tested positive for
banned substances, the local Jakarta Post reported on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The four athletes included Indonesia's gold medal-winning
cyclist Tonton Susanto, Burma's bronze medal body builder Khin
Maung Htwe, along with Kerdsumiran Nuawan and David Yinsumruay of
Thailand, gold winners of 10-meter women's air rifle and
decathlete.
</P>
<P>
General secretary of the game's organizing comittee Rudolf
S. Warouw said Tonton tested positive for the stimulant
fencamfamine after winning gold for the 40-kilometer indivedual
time trial.
</P>
<P>
Tonton would be stripped of the gold for the 40-kilometer
event, but he could keep his another gold medal he won in the road
race as he had tested negative after that event.
</P>
<P>
Warouw said initial urine samples for the three other athletes
had tested positive.
</P>
<P>
However, no action would be taken against them until the
athletes' national sports bodies approved requests for tests of a
second batch of urine sample. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
