<HEADLINE> Share Prices in Indonesia Fall Sharply </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, October 29 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Jakarta
Stock Exchange (JSX) plunged sharply by 8.59 percent or 42.12
points to a new low of 447.99 points Tuesday, brokers here said
today.
</P>
<P>
The panic selling by most investors was triggered by the
overnight plunge in Wall Street Monday and another crash of the
Hong Kong Stock Exchange Tuesday, said the brokers.
</P>
<P>
Most stock brokers in Jakarta said stocks across the board
became sell-off targets of foreign and local fund managers,
forcing the local main price gauge to fall steeply.
</P>
<P>
David Chang, head of research at Trimegah Securities, said the
fall of regional stock markets several months ago had perforated
the global market.
</P>
<P>
He said stock markets in Southeast Asian countries were badly
hit as they bore the brunt of the currency crisis in the region,
triggered by the devaluation of the Thai baht in early July.
</P>
<P>
"Now the Asian virus has spread to the world," Chang said,
referring to the fall of global stock markets.
</P>
<P>
"The general feeling is that we cannot do much. We just lie low
and find out what the corporate problems are and try to cope with
those problems," Chang added.
</P>
<P>
Most securities analysts said that it was a really difficult
time for the Jakarta stock market. "It is very difficult to
estimate when the Jakarta market will recover," one analyst said.
</P>
<P>
President Soeharto confirmed Tuesday that Singapore is ready to
offer 10 billion U.S. dollars to Indonesia to help it overcome its
monetary crisis. Malaysia and Japan have also said they will
assist Indonesia in dealing with the monetary crisis.
</P>
<P>
The value of rupiah has dropped by about 50 percent against the
U.S. dollar this year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
