months of this year, the zone approved 59 overseas-funded projects
with an investment of 360 million U.S. dollars, 290 million of
which is foreign funding. But, actually 410 million U.S. dollars
have already been spent, indicating that the zone has entered a
mature stage of development with foreign investment.
</P>
