original contracts by 124 million U.S. dollars in the first nine
months of this year, Gao said, adding that three foreign-funded
projects in the industrial sector also will spend about 30 million
U.S. dollars in additional contracts.
</P>
<P>
In another development, 15 overseas-backed projects with a
combined investment of 402 million U.S. dollars have been
submitted to the State Planning Commission for approval, Gao said.
</P>
<P>
During the first nine months, 24 overseas-funded industrial
enterprises with a 470-million-dollar capital investment have
become operational, he said, adding that the number is expected to
reach 30 by the end of this year. 
