dealing specifically with foreign affairs was the second since
the joint commission was established last year.
</P>
<P>
Issues addressed at the meeting included the setting up of an
agreement that will allow spouses of diplomats in either country
to be gainfully employed, handling of tax refunds from purchases
by diplomats, clearance of flights.
</P>
<P>
On bilateral matters the committee discussed the general
outline of double taxation and the protection of investment.
