<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, October 29 (Xinhua) -- The American Business Corporation
for Development Inc. (ABCD) will set up a 350-million-dollar joint
venture fertilizer plant in Bangladesh, a local newspaper reported
here today.
</P>
<P>
The ABCD had proposed to provide complete financing for the
project and required no guarantee from the government, the
Financial Express said, adding that the planned Shahjalal
Fertilizer Plant would be developed and operated in joint venture
with the Bangladesh Chemical Industries corporation.
</P>
<P>
The technology offered by the ABCD for the plant to be set up
in Sylhet district, 208 km from Dhaka, would be the state-of-art
and provide Bangladesh with most modern, efficient and
technologically advanced facility available in the world.
</P>
<P>
The ABCD, a consortium of Carter Development Inc. of Colorado
and the Global Market Strategies of New Jersey of the United
States, will also upgrade and keep operational the existing
Fenchuganj Fertilizer Plant in Sylhet until the new fertilizer
plant becomes operational, the newspaper reported.
</P>
<P>
The ABCD has also committed that all the employees of
Fenchuganj facility would be offered employment at the new plant,
besides an additional 1,500 full time employees. It would also
hire 2,000 workers during the construction period.
</P>
<P>
The existing housing for the workers and their families will be
completely renovated and upgraded, and new housing will be built
under the proposal submitted by the ABCD.  
