<HEADLINE> World Bank Finances Land Management Project in Brazil </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, October 28 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank today
approved a loan of 55 million U.S. dollars to finance the land
management III project in Brazil, which aimed to control erosion
and increase small farmers' productivity.
</P>
<P>
The project will promote modern forms of sustainable land
management as well as soil, water and forest conservation, and
help increase income of thousands of farm families in the state of
Sao Paulo.
</P>
<P>
This project will include about 1,500 small river basins in an
area of about 4.5 million hectares, which is about 30 percent of
the farm land, benefiting 90,000 farmers.
</P>
<P>
The total cost of the project is some 124.7 million dollars, of
which the state government of Sao Paulo will contribute 66.7
million dollars. 
