<HEADLINE> India Adopts New Gold Import Policy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, October 29 (Xinhua) -- The Indian government has
formally notified its decision to liberalize import of gold as
well as silver, the local press said today.
</P>
<P>
With the notification issued Monday, agencies designated by the
government would now be able to import the precious metals without
any license for sale in the domestic market.
</P>
<P>
Under the old import regime, a very limited number of agencies
could import gold and silver through a special import license
route for sale only to jewelry producers in the country.
</P>
<P>
Payment of duty could be made in rupees under the new import
policy instead of in U.S. dollars as stipulated by the old regime.
 
