<HEADLINE> Increasing Cultural Activities In Northeast China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, October 29 (Xinhua) -- Northeast China's Liaoning
Province has spent 150 million yuan on cultural activities in
cities and towns along its border in recent years.
</P>
<P>
Five years ago, the province began its culture-promotion
project to develop public activities in six cities, 26 counties,
and two state-level economic development zones along its 306-km
border with the Democratic People's Republic of Korea.
</P>
<P>
The public in all counties and cities along the border now have
culture parks, cultural centers, museums, and indoor swimming
pools, and six cinemas and 40 dance halls have been opened for the
public.
</P>
<P>
A number of art troupes for the dragon dance, brass bands,
choruses, and kite shows have been formed and have taken part in
many international cultural exchange programs and performanced at
national exhibitions. 
