<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Exports of Bangladeshi EPZs Increase in 1st Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, October 29 (Xinhua) -- The enterprises of Bangladesh's
two export processing zones (EPZs) have exported goods worth 6.9
billion taka (156.8 million U.S. dollars) during the first quarter
of the current fiscal year (starting from July 1, 1997), showing
an increase of 28.44 percent compared to that of the corresponding
period of the last fiscal year, sources from the EPZ said here
today.
</P>
<P>
The exported items include electronics and electrical goods,
textiles and leather goods, finishing reel and gold shaft, metal
products, garments and its accessories, caps, tents, toys, terry
towel, plastic goods and paper products, according to the sources.
</P>
<P>
At present, there are two export processing zones in this South
Asian country -- the Dhaka and Chittagong.
</P>
<P>
Seventy-six industries are now in operation in the Chittagong
Export Processing Zone with an investment of 201.69 million
dollars. Another 53 industries are in implementing stage, while 28
industries are operating in the Dhaka Exert Processing Zone with
an investment of about 63 million dollars, and another 40
industries will be started their operation within a short period
of time.  
</P>
</TEXT>
