<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Crimes Reduce Sharply in Kathmandu Valley </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, October 29 (Xinhua) -- The crime rate in the
Kathmandu Valley has decreased so far this year by 77.13 percent
compared with the previous year, Nepali newspapers reported today.
</P>
<P>
Traffic accidents and deaths caused thereby have dropped by
20.93 percent and 22.72 percent respectively, the reports quoted
police statistics as saying.
</P>
<P>
The police attribute these changes to vigorous beat and special
patrols, new methods used in duty and surveillance of suspected
criminal elements.
</P>
<P>
During the country's largest Dashain Festival which ended
recently, only eight crime cases occurred in the Valley as against
35 over the same period of last year, a senior police officer
said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile crimes have dropped by 10.25 percent in the Valley in
the month of Aswin (September/October) as compared with the month
of Bhadra (August/September), the officer said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
