<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Shares Keep Leap at Midday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 29 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong stocks kept a
big rise this noon on the heels of a 17.3-percent leap at the
opening this morning, enhancing hopes that the market is bottoming
out.
</P>
<P>
The key Hang Seng Index rose 1,509.85 points, or 14.3 percent,
to close at 10569.74 at midday.
</P>
<P>
The market recovered at the opening this morning in the wake of
the biggest one-day gain ever on Wall Street overnight. It surged
17.3 percent at the opening today, with the key Hang Seng Index
leaping 1,570.24 points to 10,630.13 in the first two minutes of
trade.
</P>
<P>
On Tuesday, the Index nosedived to a record single-day crash
following a huge Monday night plunge on Wall Street, dropping 13.7
percent with its worst fall of 1,438.31 points to close at
9,059.89.  
