<HEADLINE> Russia Enjoys Progress in Public Health </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, October (Xinhua) -- Russia has enjoyed a decline in
death rate and a rise in birth rate in recent years, Public Health
Minister Tatyana Dmitriyeva said today in Jekaterinburg.
</P>
<P>
This shows the gradual progress of Russia's public health work
and the improved health condition of the Russian population, a
more convincing sign of national stability than the slowdown of
inflation rate or rise of gross domestic product (GDP), the
minister said at a national congress.
</P>
<P>
The minister said that since the beginning of the year,
incidence of 28 kinds of diseases has dropped or been controlled,
and no poliomyelitis cases reported. In addition, incidence of
diphtheria and measles were down respectively by three folds and
69 percent in 1997, Dmitriyeva said.  
</P>
