<HEADLINE> Police Arrest 15 More Rebels Responsible for Colombo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Colombo, October 29 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan police in the
northern city of Vavuniya Tuesday arrested 15 Tamil rebels who
were involved in the massive bombing of downtown Colombo on
October 15, police sources said here today.
</P>
<P>
They were alleged to have been responsible for building a
special compartment on the chassis of a truck purchased in Kandy,
Central Province, by their agents some months ago.
</P>
<P>
The truck was carrying bags of rice in disguise when the
explosives on the truck exploded, causing heavy casualties and
severe damage to downtown landmark buildings in the capital.
</P>
<P>
Police said the 15 suspects made the compartment to conceal the
explosives under the special direction of the Liberation Tigers of
Tamil Eelam, which was blamed for the attack.
</P>
<P>
Police added that some other people who were involved in making
such compartments for trucks were also in custody.
</P>
<P>
Security has been tightened up both in Colombo and the other
cities in the country following the powerful blast nearly half
month ago. Colombo police have arrested several key suspects for
the bombing.
</P>
<P>
On October 25, the security forces sealed off the capital and
conducted a massive crack-down operation in which around 1,000
people were detained. The majority of them were later released.
</P>
</TEXT>
