<HEADLINE> City in Three Gorges Area Aims High in Rebuilding </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, October 29 (Xinhua) -- Wanxian City aims to become a
regional economic center as a result of the massive resettlement
for the Three Gorges Project, sources here said.
</P>
<P>
Wanxian, covering 29,500 square kilometers in the eastern part
of Chongqing, is a big grain production center with more than 90
percent of its population engaged in farming.
</P>
<P>
More than 800,000 people are being resettled and part of the
city's urban area will be removed to make way for constructing the
dam project.
</P>
<P>
According to Gu Wenxing, a leading official of Wanxian, the
resettlement has given the city an opportunity to benefit from a
central government's investment of one billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
In the next 10 years, the central and local governments are
expected to invest more than five billion yuan annually for
resettlement and rebuilding.
</P>
<P>
Gu told Xinhua that the city expects to become a prosperous,
regional center in industrial, communications, financial,
commercial, tourism and information fields in eastern Chongqing,
the youngest municipality in China.
</P>
<P>
Wanxian has been granted preferential policies to promote the
local economy, he said, noting that the new residents of the city
will become a manufacturing center for many name-brand products.
</P>
<P>
The city government has also drawn up plans to tap its unique
tourism resources and hopes to make it a backbone industry.
</P>
<P>
Gu said that the city has invested more than 200 million yuan
in the Wanxian Yangtze River Bridge Project and road extensions,
and another 600 million yuan in Wuqiao Airport.
</P>
<P>
One billion yuan is expected to be invested in railway
construction between Wanxian and Daxian, and a deep-water port
capable of handling 1,500-ton-class vessels, he said.
</P>
<P>
The city's rebuilding is an important part of economic
development in Chongqing as well as the southwestern part of the
country, Gu said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
