<HEADLINE> NATO Supports Ukraine's Integration with Europe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, October 28 (Xinhua) -- Ukraine's cooperation with the
North Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO) is an important step in
the process of European Integration, says Don McConnen, head of
the NATO political committee.
</P>
<P>
McConnen made the remark at a press conference before ending a
two-day visit here as the leader of a NATO delegation.
</P>
<P>
The alliance is planning to enhance ties with eastern European
countries, including Russia and Ukraine, he said.
</P>
<P>
During his stay, McConnen discussed with Ukrainian officials
the necessity of stepping up joint actions to improve the
implementation of the Ukrainian-NATO distinctive partnership
charter signed in July.
</P>
<P>
He told Boris Olinyk, chairman of the Committee for Foreign
Affairs and Relations with Commonwealth of Independent States
(CIS) Nations, that it is feasible to open a Ukrainian military
mission for communications at NATO's headquarters in Brussels.
</P>
<P>
McConnen also proposed arranging various seminars on military
development in Ukraine.
</P>
<P>
Olinyk said: "Ukrainian citizens, particularly the Ukrainian
parliament, have different opinions on the Ukrainian-NATO
relations and NATO's expansion."
</P>
<P>
However, he said, Ukraine seeks to integrate into the European
community and at the same time maintain its own
sovereignty. Cooperation between the two sides was in accordance
with Ukraine's national interests and security.
</P>
<P>
"We will integrate into European structures to ensure our
sovereignty, even though not everyone welcomes this process," he
stressed. 
</P>
