<HEADLINE> More Tourist Facilities in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, October 29 (Xinhua) -- China's tourist facilities are
more than adequate to accommodate the growth in domestic tourism,
a high-ranking official said here at a travel industry fair.
</P>
<P>
According to Chen Wendong, vice-chairman of the China National
Tourism Administration, the country has 4,960 travel agencies, of
which 3,995 work for domestic tourists and the rest for
international travelers.
</P>
<P>
There are 4,418 tourist hotels, of which 2,349 are
star-rated. Budget-conscious domestic tourists can stay in
lower-priced hostels which are usually run by government
organizations and enterprises, Chen said.
</P>
<P>
At a domestic tourist fair which closed last weekend in Dalian,
Chen said tourism programs are diversifying to meet the growing
need of the domestic travelers.
</P>
<P>
Chinese tourists are flocking to newly built holiday resorts
for such purposes as skiing and other sports, ecological
activities and personal health. 
</P>
