<HEADLINE> Asia's Largest Flower Trading Center Being Built in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 29 (Xinhua) -- A flower trading center with a
floor space of 46,000 square meters, the largest of its kind in
Asia, is under construction in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The project is scheduled for completion by the end of this year.
</P>
<P>
The 220-million-yuan project has been jointly funded by the
Holland Europe-Asia International Trade Company and the Beijing
Sun Palace Township Agricultural, Industrial and Commercial Corp.
</P>
<P>
The center in the Chaoyang District will include a flower
supermarket, an auction hall, an exhibition hall and an
international agricultural information center equipped with a
computer network.
</P>
<P>
Other support facilities such as banks and transport services
will be incorporated into the center.
</P>
<P>
International practices will be followed at the flower auction,
according to Yang Bin, president of the Holland-based company.
</P>
<P>
Official figures show that the trade volume of flowers in
Beijing had increased eightfold in the 1991-96 period.
</P>
<P>
Sales at the flower shops in the city, which now number 256,
were 100 million yuan in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Beijing now has three large flower wholesale markets, covering
more than 27,000 square meters.
</P>
<P>
A local survey predicts that flower sales will go up 30 percent
this year.
</P>
<P>
The trading center is expected to play an active role in
boosting the development of country's fledgling floral
industry. 
</P>
</TEXT>
