<HEADLINE> Foreign Investment Pours into Croatia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZAGREB, October 28 (Xinhua) -- Increasing foreign investment is
pouring into Croatia encouraged by stability, improved investment
environment and the government's active measures.
</P>
<P>
Croatia received a total of 80.07 million U.S. dollars in
foreign investment in 1993, and this dropped to 63.28 million in
1994. In 1995, the figure bounced up to 85.16 million, the
National Bank reported today.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, foreign investment soared to 492 million dollars,
nearly five times that in 1995.
</P>
<P>
Foreign investors mainly came from 15 countries including
Austria, Switzerland, Sweden, Belgium, Germany, the United States,
Denmark and Italy.
</P>
<P>
The investments went into more than 60 projects in the food,
cement and electronic industries.
</P>
<P>
Some countries have also shown interest in Croatia's oil
industry. With increasing stablization of the national situation
and continued economic development, Croatia is expected to attract
more foreign investment. 
</P>
