<HEADLINE> Albania, Italy Cooperate to Battle Mafia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, October 28 (Xinhua) -- Italy's national anti-Mafia
procuratorate will establish an office in Albania's procurator
general's office in the foreseeable future.
</P>
<P>
This is a provision in an agreement signed here between Luigi
Vigni, Italy's national anti-Mafia procurator, and Arb En Rakip,
Albania's procurator general. It also allows for Albania's
procurator general's office to set up an office in Italy's
national anti-Mafia procuratorate.
</P>
<P>
The two sides will exchange operational information on Mafia
organizations and provide judicial assistance for each other's law
enforcement officials.
</P>
<P>
Albania wants Italy to provide material and technical aid for
its battle against Mafia members.
</P>
<P>
Since 1991, a large number of Albanian immigrants have
illegally entered into Italy. Some have become members of
underworld groups in southern Italy.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, organized crime in Albania has increased.
</P>
<P>
Vigni, who made a two-day visit to Albania, said Albania's
Mafia in Italy were very powerful and commanded Italian criminal
groups in many cities. Albanian Mafia members had been involved in
drug trafficking, prostitution, car theft and arms trading, said
Vigni. 
</P>
