<HEADLINE> Emerson Builds Compressor Plant in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SUZHOU, October 29 (Xinhua) -- Construction of a solely
Emerson-invested scroll compressor plant started Monday in the
industrial park in Suzhou, a renowned scenic city in east China's
Jiangsu Province.
</P>
<P>
The Copeland (Suzhou) Scroll Compressor Plant will be built
with an investment of 180 million US dollars from the Copeland
Corporation, an affiliate of the Emerson Electric Co..
</P>
<P>
Emerson Vice-Chairman Robert W. Staley and Copeland's Chairman
Robert J. Novello attended Monday's foundation stone laying
ceremony and announced that the plant, to become operational in 18
months, will employ 1,200 workers.
</P>
<P>
The plant will cover a floor space of 140,000 sq m, and will
have an annual production capacity of one million scroll
compressors for air-conditioners. Its products will sell on the
domestic market and in east Asian countries.
</P>
<P>
So far, Emerson, and its subsidiaries have 10 solely-funded
companies and seven joint ventures in China. The new plant
prepresents the company's largest investment in the Asian-Pacific
Region.
</P>
<P>
Emerson Electric had 11 billion US dollars in sales in 1996,
ranking 45th in the Fortune 500. Copeland Co., a well-known
air-conditioner manufacturer, became its subsidiary in 1986.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
