<HEADLINE> Ericsson to Expand GSM Communication Network in East China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, October 29 (Xinhua) -- Sweden's Ericsson has signed a
contract for the GSM communications network in east China's
Shandong province that is estimated to cost 140 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time for the province to open its
communications market to overseas investors on such a large scale.
</P>
<P>
It is expected to be built in the first quarter of next year to
expand the present network by adding 12 exchange facilities and
711 base stations.
</P>
<P>
The new communications network will cover the province and have
a capacity of 1.4 million lines. 
