<HEADLINE> Menem Rules Out Economic Crisis In Argentina </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, October 28 (Xinhua) -- Argentina`s President,
Carlos Menem, has ruled out a crisis similar to that of December
1994 which affected his country and Mexico.
</P>
<P>
The present security was based on the fact that "the economy
and finances (of Argentina) are very solid and stable," he
explained.
</P>
<P>
Menem said the present situation is different and his
government is taking the necessary measures to prevent the
financial and currency turmoil occurring in Southeast Asia from
affecting Argentina.
</P>
<P>
The stock market in Buenos Aries plunged Monday 13.72 percent
in its leading shares, the strongest decline since January 1990.
</P>
<P>
Today the behavior of stocks is still uncertain. Stock values
of the leading companies were climbing back and were up from the
previous day by 1.27 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
