<HEADLINE> Primorac Calls for European-Chinese Team Contest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, October 28 (Xinhua) -- Newly-crowned World Cup champion
Zoran Primorac called for a team contest in table tennis between
Europe and the traditional powerhouse China to make men's team
events more competitive.
</P>
<P>
After his triumph in Sunday's World Cup final against China's
former world champion Kong Linghui, the 28-year-old Croatian said
that only an united European team would give them the chance to
beat China in men's team events.
</P>
<P>
Like in golf's Ryder Cup, where Europe beat the United States
for the title this September, a team combining all European
talents would have an edge to challenge China's domination in
men's team competition, he said. 
