<HEADLINE> Turkish Foreign Minister Visits Albania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, October 28 (Xinhua) -- Turkish Foreign Minister Ismail
Cem and Albanian Foreign Minister Paskal Milo today discussed
economic cooperation between their two countries.
</P>
<P>
The two foreign ministers reviewed cooperation in finance,
agriculture, tourism, education and culture between Turkey and
Albania.
</P>
<P>
They agreed to hold the meeting of the Turkey-Albania Joint
Committee for Economic Cooperation as soon as possible to discuss
the establishment of free economic zones and promote regional
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The two sides decided to hold an expert-level meeting January
next year to review the implementation of the existing cooperation
programs between the two countries and assess Turkey's financial
aid to Albania.
</P>
<P>
The two ministers also signed a cooperation accord between
their ministries.
</P>
<P>
Cem, during his a one-day visit to Albania today, also met
Albanian President Rexhep Mejdani, parliament speaker Skender
Gjinushi and Prime Minister Fatos Nano.
</P>
<P>
The Albanian side hoped Cem's visit would help promote
Albania's integration with Europe. 
</P>
