<HEADLINE> Baltic Countries to Cooperate in Fight Against Crimes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WARSAW, October 28 (Xinhua) -- The 5th Cooperation Conference
of Baltic Countries, which ended here today, decided to enhance
cooperation among the countries and crack down on organized
crimes, embezzlement and money laundering.
</P>
<P>
The resolution, released after the meeting, said the Baltic
countries should make the anti-crime fight a main area of
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
More than 350 representatives from the Baltic countries and
international organizations participated in the two-day meeting.
</P>
<P>
Stressing that they must combat drug trafficking, and smuggling
of women and children, the resolution noted that the Baltic
countries would continue to work for the security of the whole
region.
</P>
<P>
The document appealed to the European Union for support to the
efforts of the Baltic countries in joining the organization and
also demonstrated their need to develop cooperation with Russia.
</P>
