<HEADLINE> Meeting For Hemispheric Free Trade Area Starts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANACASTE, Costa Rica, October 28 (Xinhua) -- A preparatory
meeting for the Free Trade Area of the Americas (FTAA) was held on
Tuesday, which may be the last opportunity for delegates to
discuss the agenda of the hemispheric presidential summit next
year in Chile.
</P>
<P>
Representatives from 34 countries across the American continent
will try to discuss the related issue of the creation of a
hemispheric free trade area.
</P>
<P>
Organizers said that 12 work teams are to be reduced to six or
seven and it is also expected that representatives will create a
secretariat in charge of negotiations.
</P>
<P>
They said that Rio de Janeiro and Miami are most likely to be
chosen as the headquarters for the FTAA Secretariat. 
</P>
</TEXT>
