<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Northeast China Attracting More Foreign Investors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, October 29 (Xinhua) -- Northeast China's Liaoning
province, a heavy industrial production base, has become the
fourth largest user of foreign funds in the country, after
Jiangsu, Shanghai and Guangdong.
</P>
<P>
Liaoning has overtaken Fujian and Shandong provinces, according
to Du Qiugen, deputy director of the Provincial Department of
Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Du says that Liaoning had 1.6 billion US dollars worth of
overseas investment during the January-September period, 57
percent more than for the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Some 14 percent of the foreign funds were used for
infrastructure projects. Old state enterprises, which are often
not profit makers, have attracted 440 million US dollars, he
added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
