<HEADLINE> Keller, Hamm Named U.S. Best Soccer Athletes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, October 28 (Xinhua) -- Kasey Keller and Mia Hamm
were named the 1997 U.S. Soccer male and female Athletes of the
Year respectively, the U.S. soccer federation announced on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Keller, the first goalkeeper in the 14-year history of the
award, surrendered just six goals and run up a span of 562
consecutive minutes without conceding a goal in America's 1997
World Cup qualifying matches.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, Keller also helped the English club Leicester City
promote into the Premiership and to an English Cup title last
season.
</P>
<P>
The 25-year-old Hamm became the first four-time winner of the
award after scoring 17 goals in 12 games in 1997. 
</P>
