<HEADLINE> Foreign Investments Rise in Colombia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA, October 28 (Xinhua) -- Foreign investments
in Colombia reached 1.41 billion U.S. dollars from January to July
this year, an 88 percent increase from the total 756 million
dollars the country received last year.
</P>
<P>
Colombia's Corporation for Investments said the most dynamic
months were April and July during which 301.5 million and 353
million dollars entered the country.
</P>
<P>
The sectors most attractive to investors were power, gas and
water supply.
</P>
<P>
A considerable amount of foreign investment also went to the
manufacturing sector, mining, finance, insurance, real state and
services.
</P>
<P>
The sectors that suffered an investment setback in the first
half of this year were timber, furniture, textiles, leather goods
and hotels.
</P>
<P>
The main investor in Colombia is the United States which poured
into the country 325 million dollars in the January-July period.
</P>
</TEXT>
