<HEADLINE> Sudan Wishes to Improve Relations with Egypt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KHARTOUM, October 28 (Xinhua) -- Sudanese Minister of State at
the Foreign Ministry Mustafa Othman Ismail announced that Sudan
welcomes any initiative aimed at overcoming obstacles and
improving Sudanese-Egyptian relations.
</P>
<P>
According to local reports today, the minister said Sudan was
convinced that the best means to improve Sudanese-Egyptian
relations was direct dialogue to determine the obstacles that
obstruct the historical and geographic ties.
</P>
<P>
The minister welcomed efforts to promote such dialogue, adding
that Sudan believes in joint actions within the framework of the
League of Arab States or that of the Organization of African Unity
for resolving the problems.
</P>
<P>
Such an approach, however, does not prevent bilateral or
trilateral contacts for a solution, he said.
</P>
<P>
South Africa President Nelson Mandela had, during the visit to
South Africa by Sudanese President Omar al-Bashir last August,
proposed an initiative for the eradication of differences between
the Sudan and Egypt.
</P>
<P>
Sudanese-Egyptian relations have in recent years seen mounting
tension over disputed border areas.
</P>
<P>
In addition, Egypt has been accusing Sudan of supporting
Egyptian terrorists and involving in an attempt on the life of
Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak during the African summit in
1995. Sudan promptly denied the allegation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
