<DOCNO> XIE19971029.0304 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Urges Int'l Community to Assist Developing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, October 28 (Xinhua) -- It was necessary for the
international community, especially the developed countries, to
take measures to assist the development of the enterprises of the
developing countries, Chinese delegate Yuan Shaofu said here
today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the Second Committee (Economic and Financial) of
the 52nd session of the General Assembly, Yuan Shaofu said
enterprises were important players in economic and social
development. Small and medium enterprises in developed countries
played an important role in generating tax revenue, creating
employment, contributing to social stability and represent the
potential for economic growth.
</P>
<P>
Yuan said all enterprises in the developing countries were
small and medium sized, due to the near non-existence of large
transnational corporations. In recent years, the development of
enterprises had been accorded more and more attention from the
international community.
</P>
<P>
Yuan said that in view of the fact that almost all enterprises
in developing countries were small and medium sized, which
suffered from technical backwardness, lacked of human and
financial resources, and lagged far behind the level that
enterprises in developed countries had reached, assistance in this
regard could take a variety of forms which could at least include
the following: joint venture, stock participation,
sub-contracting, technological transfer, strategic alliances and
licensing.
</P>
<P>
Such kind of assistance, he said, was indispensable because
interdependence was also expressed in the relationship between the
enterprises of developed countries and those of developing
countries, given the increasing globalization and liberalization
of the world economy.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese delegate said industrial development occupied an
important position in the development of national economies. it
was the key to the process of modernization. In the globalization
process, the issue of industrialization of the developing
countries was particularly important.
</P>
<P>
Yuan stressed a country's own efforts were of course
indispensable for its industrialization process. But at the same
time, support from the international community was also necessary.
Assisting the developing countries to achieve industrial
development and economic growth should be a major component in
international development cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Yuan expressed the hope the United Nations Industrial
Development Organization would further strengthen its mandated
role, so as to continue to contribute to the promotion of
international cooperation in the industrial sector, and to assist
the developing countries in achieving the elimination of poverty
and the revitalization of their economies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
