<HEADLINE> Dow Jumps 337 Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, October 28 (Xinhua) -- The Dow Jones industrial
average soared more than 337 points today, its biggest one-day
gain ever, as investors shrugged off a historic market plunge on
Monday and instead jumped at the cheap prices available.
</P>
<P>
Volume shot to a record 1.1 billion shares on the New York
Stock Exchange. Broad-market indexes, meanwhile, staged an
incredible recovery from an early morning slump.
</P>
<P>
The Dow jumped 337.17 points to 7,498.32 at the closing.
</P>
<P>
Winners outpaced falling stocks by a 11-to-8 margin on the New
York Stock Exchange, where the volume shot to 1.195 billion shares
as against 685.5 million in the previous session.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500-stock list rose 39.24 to 916.22, and
the NYSE composite index rose 19.45 at 482.66.
</P>
<P>
The Nasdaq composite index rose 65.25 to 1,600.34, and the
American Stock Exchange composite index rose 9.86 to 670.27.
</P>
<P>
Stock plunged at the opening bell today, sliding about 178
points in the first minutes of trading.
</P>
<P>
The Dow fell 554.26 points Monday, its biggest point drop ever,
while the Nasdaq was down 7 percent.
</P>
<P>
IBM led the Dow, after it indicated that it planned to buy
back more of its own stocks.
</P>
<P>
In addition, news from The Conference Board that consumer
confidence in the economy fell sharply in October also give sume
support. That helped reinforce expectations that the Federal
Reserve wouldn't move to raise short-term interest rates in the
near future.  
</P>
</TEXT>
