<HEADLINE> European Shares Cut Losses, But Still Down Sharply </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, October 28 (Xinhua) -- Leading stock markets in Europe
all slashed their early losses today, boosted by Wall Street's
remarkable recovery, but still ended sharply down.
</P>
<P>
Nerves steadied on the London market after the Dow staged a
dramatic about-turn which turned a loss into a gain. In response,
the FTSE 100 index stemmed its decline and ended just 85.3 points
down at 4,755.4.
</P>
<P>
The index had tumbled 457.9 points or more than 9 percent at
one stage to a low of 4,382.8 before staging a recovery and ended
off the day's lows.
</P>
<P>
On the Frankfurt market, which ends before Wall Street opens,
US and Asian losses continued to upset German shares, with the
DAX-30 index plunging by 311.90 points to end 8 percent lower at
3,567.22.
</P>
<P>
Paris' CAC-40 index dropped by 4.27 percent, or 118.31 points,
to end the day at 2,651.33. French shares fell in line with world
markets which were knocked by steep losses in America and the Far
East. 
</P>
</TEXT>
