<HEADLINE> President Jiang Zemin Arrives in Washington </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, October 28 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang
Zemin arrived here today for a state visit to the United States at
the invitation of President Bill Clinton.
</P>
<P>
It is the first state visit by a Chinese head of state to the
U.S. in 12 years, a historical event seen as a milestone in the
Sino-American relations.
</P>
<P>
Jiang is to receive a 21-gun solute welcome ceremony Wednesday
morning in the South Lawn of the White house, which is to be
followed by a summit meeting at noon and a state diner in the
evening. 
</P>
