<HEADLINE> European Union Pledges Economic Aid to PNA </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, October 28 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU) has
pledged to provide economic aid to the Palestinian National
Authority (PNA), said PNA Finance Minister Mohammed Zuhdi
Nashashibi in Gaza today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to reporters upon his return from his recent visit to
Brussels, Nashashibi said that the EU has agreed to provide an
economic aid of 30 million U.S. dollars to the PNA, the Jerusalem
Media and Communication Cernter (JMCC) reported.
</P>
<P>
He added that the EU will also grant the PNA a loan of 100
million dollars.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the finance minister disclosed that the budget
deficit of the PNA has amounted to 116 million dollars due to
Israel's closure on the Palestinian self-ruled areas, according to
JMCC.
</P>
<P>
He warned that the deficit will continue to rise if Israel does
not lift the closure.
</P>
<P>
Israel sealed off the PNA territories in the wake of suicide
bombings in Jerusalem on July 30, blocking Palestinian workers and
vehicles from entering Israel.
</P>
<P>
So far, internal closure has been lifted in some cities, but
the total closure remains intact. 
</P>
</TEXT>
